{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":612,"text":"For the next 16 minutes,\nI'm going to take you on a journey"},{"time":3398,"text":"that is probably\nthe biggest dream of humanity:"},{"time":6508,"text":"to understand the code of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9072,"text":"So for me, everything started\nmany, many years ago"},{"time":11839,"text":"when I met the first 3D printer."},{"time":14586,"text":"The concept was fascinating."},{"time":16284,"text":"A 3D printer needs three elements:"},{"time":18330,"text":"a bit of information, some\nraw material, some energy,"},{"time":22488,"text":"and it can produce any object\nthat was not there before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26517,"text":"I was doing physics,\nI was coming back home"},{"time":28678,"text":"and I realized that I actually\nalways knew a 3D printer."},{"time":32140,"text":"And everyone does."},{"time":33500,"text":"It was my mom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34682,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":35707,"text":"My mom takes three elements:"},{"time":38145,"text":"a bit of information, which is between\nmy father and my mom in this case,"},{"time":42142,"text":"raw elements and energy\nin the same media, that is food,"},{"time":46323,"text":"and after several months, produces me."},{"time":48855,"text":"And I was not existent before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50691,"text":"So apart from the shock of my mom\ndiscovering that she was a 3D printer,"},{"time":54477,"text":"I immediately got mesmerized\nby that piece,"},{"time":59239,"text":"the first one, the information."},{"time":60980,"text":"What amount of information does it take"},{"time":63255,"text":"to build and assemble a human?"},{"time":65215,"text":"Is it much? Is it little?"},{"time":66813,"text":"How many thumb drives can you fill?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":69017,"text":"Well, I was studying physics\nat the beginning"},{"time":71665,"text":"and I took this approximation of a human\nas a gigantic Lego piece."},{"time":77286,"text":"So, imagine that the building\nblocks are little atoms"},{"time":81095,"text":"and there is a hydrogen here,\na carbon here, a nitrogen here."},{"time":85772,"text":"So in the first approximation,"},{"time":87367,"text":"if I can list the number of atoms\nthat compose a human being,"},{"time":91734,"text":"I can build it."},{"time":93145,"text":"Now, you can run some numbers"},{"time":95198,"text":"and that happens to be\nquite an astonishing number."},{"time":98499,"text":"So the number of atoms,"},{"time":101280,"text":"the file that I will save in my thumb\ndrive to assemble a little baby,"},{"time":106059,"text":"will actually fill an entire Titanic\nof thumb drives --"},{"time":110750,"text":"multiplied 2,000 times."},{"time":113957,"text":"This is the miracle of life."},{"time":117382,"text":"Every time you see from now on\na pregnant lady,"},{"time":120018,"text":"she's assembling the biggest\namount of information"},{"time":122898,"text":"that you will ever encounter."},{"time":124478,"text":"Forget big data, forget\nanything you heard of."},{"time":127452,"text":"This is the biggest amount\nof information that exists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130357,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":134214,"text":"But nature, fortunately, is much smarter\nthan a young physicist,"},{"time":138882,"text":"and in four billion years, managed\nto pack this information"},{"time":142482,"text":"in a small crystal we call DNA."},{"time":145605,"text":"We met it for the first time in 1950\nwhen Rosalind Franklin,"},{"time":149941,"text":"an amazing scientist, a woman,"},{"time":151521,"text":"took a picture of it."},{"time":152934,"text":"But it took us more than 40 years\nto finally poke inside a human cell,"},{"time":158146,"text":"take out this crystal,"},{"time":159772,"text":"unroll it, and read it for the first time."},{"time":163615,"text":"The code comes out to be\na fairly simple alphabet,"},{"time":166880,"text":"four letters: A, T, C and G."},{"time":170676,"text":"And to build a human,\nyou need three billion of them."},{"time":174933,"text":"Three billion."},{"time":176136,"text":"How many are three billion?"},{"time":177739,"text":"It doesn't really make\nany sense as a number, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":180525,"text":"So I was thinking how\nI could explain myself better"},{"time":184634,"text":"about how big and enormous this code is."},{"time":187708,"text":"But there is -- I mean,\nI'm going to have some help,"},{"time":190786,"text":"and the best person to help me\nintroduce the code"},{"time":194037,"text":"is actually the first man\nto sequence it, Dr. Craig Venter."},{"time":197583,"text":"So welcome onstage, Dr. Craig Venter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200997,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":207952,"text":"Not the man in the flesh,"},{"time":211448,"text":"but for the first time in history,"},{"time":213817,"text":"this is the genome of a specific human,"},{"time":217303,"text":"printed page-by-page, letter-by-letter:"},{"time":221087,"text":"262,000 pages of information,"},{"time":225107,"text":"450 kilograms, shipped\nfrom the United States to Canada"},{"time":229495,"text":"thanks to Bruno Bowden,\nLulu.com, a start-up, did everything."},{"time":234362,"text":"It was an amazing feat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235849,"text":"But this is the visual perception\nof what is the code of life."},{"time":240170,"text":"And now, for the first time,\nI can do something fun."},{"time":242672,"text":"I can actually poke inside it and read."},{"time":245243,"text":"So let me take an interesting\nbook ... like this one."},{"time":253077,"text":"I have an annotation;\nit's a fairly big book."},{"time":255635,"text":"So just to let you see\nwhat is the code of life."},{"time":260566,"text":"Thousands and thousands and thousands"},{"time":263981,"text":"and millions of letters."},{"time":266675,"text":"And they apparently make sense."},{"time":269095,"text":"Let's get to a specific part."},{"time":271571,"text":"Let me read it to you:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":272957,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":274002,"text":"\"AAG, AAT, ATA.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":278965,"text":"To you it sounds like mute letters,"},{"time":281056,"text":"but this sequence gives\nthe color of the eyes to Craig."},{"time":285633,"text":"I'll show you another part of the book."},{"time":287589,"text":"This is actually a little\nmore complicated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290983,"text":"Chromosome 14, book 132:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":293654,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":295768,"text":"As you might expect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297069,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302857,"text":"\"ATT, CTT, GATT.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":308329,"text":"This human is lucky,"},{"time":310040,"text":"because if you miss just\ntwo letters in this position --"},{"time":314581,"text":"two letters of our three billion --"},{"time":316482,"text":"he will be condemned\nto a terrible disease:"},{"time":318525,"text":"cystic fibrosis."},{"time":319989,"text":"We have no cure for it,\nwe don't know how to solve it,"},{"time":323426,"text":"and it's just two letters\nof difference from what we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327585,"text":"A wonderful book, a mighty book,"},{"time":331115,"text":"a mighty book that helped me understand"},{"time":333137,"text":"and show you something quite remarkable."},{"time":336480,"text":"Every one of you -- what makes\nme, me and you, you --"},{"time":340939,"text":"is just about five million of these,"},{"time":343917,"text":"half a book."},{"time":346015,"text":"For the rest,"},{"time":347702,"text":"we are all absolutely identical."},{"time":351008,"text":"Five hundred pages\nis the miracle of life that you are."},{"time":355050,"text":"The rest, we all share it."},{"time":357605,"text":"So think about that again\nwhen we think that we are different."},{"time":360538,"text":"This is the amount that we share."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363441,"text":"So now that I have your attention,"},{"time":366894,"text":"the next question is:"},{"time":368277,"text":"How do I read it?"},{"time":369452,"text":"How do I make sense out of it?"},{"time":371409,"text":"Well, for however good you can be\nat assembling Swedish furniture,"},{"time":375673,"text":"this instruction manual\nis nothing you can crack in your life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379260,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":380887,"text":"And so, in 2014, two famous TEDsters,"},{"time":384023,"text":"Peter Diamandis and Craig Venter himself,"},{"time":386587,"text":"decided to assemble a new company."},{"time":388538,"text":"Human Longevity was born,"},{"time":389974,"text":"with one mission:"},{"time":391368,"text":"trying everything we can try"},{"time":393253,"text":"and learning everything\nwe can learn from these books,"},{"time":396036,"text":"with one target --"},{"time":398862,"text":"making real the dream\nof personalized medicine,"},{"time":401687,"text":"understanding what things\nshould be done to have better health"},{"time":405478,"text":"and what are the secrets in these books."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408329,"text":"An amazing team, 40 data scientists\nand many, many more people,"},{"time":412603,"text":"a pleasure to work with."},{"time":413977,"text":"The concept is actually very simple."},{"time":416254,"text":"We're going to use a technology\ncalled machine learning."},{"time":419436,"text":"On one side, we have genomes --\nthousands of them."},{"time":423999,"text":"On the other side, we collected\nthe biggest database of human beings:"},{"time":428020,"text":"phenotypes, 3D scan, NMR --\neverything you can think of."},{"time":432340,"text":"Inside there, on these two opposite sides,"},{"time":435263,"text":"there is the secret of translation."},{"time":437729,"text":"And in the middle, we build a machine."},{"time":440801,"text":"We build a machine\nand we train a machine --"},{"time":443210,"text":"well, not exactly one machine,\nmany, many machines --"},{"time":446444,"text":"to try to understand and translate\nthe genome in a phenotype."},{"time":451362,"text":"What are those letters,\nand what do they do?"},{"time":454726,"text":"It's an approach that can\nbe used for everything,"},{"time":457497,"text":"but using it in genomics\nis particularly complicated."},{"time":460514,"text":"Little by little we grew and we wanted\nto build different challenges."},{"time":463814,"text":"We started from the beginning,\nfrom common traits."},{"time":466570,"text":"Common traits are comfortable\nbecause they are common,"},{"time":469197,"text":"everyone has them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470405,"text":"So we started to ask our questions:"},{"time":472923,"text":"Can we predict height?"},{"time":474985,"text":"Can we read the books\nand predict your height?"},{"time":477186,"text":"Well, we actually can,"},{"time":478361,"text":"with five centimeters of precision."},{"time":480178,"text":"BMI is fairly connected to your lifestyle,"},{"time":483337,"text":"but we still can, we get in the ballpark,\neight kilograms of precision."},{"time":487225,"text":"Can we predict eye color?"},{"time":488480,"text":"Yeah, we can."},{"time":489662,"text":"Eighty percent accuracy."},{"time":491466,"text":"Can we predict skin color?"},{"time":493348,"text":"Yeah we can, 80 percent accuracy."},{"time":495813,"text":"Can we predict age?"},{"time":498121,"text":"We can, because apparently,\nthe code changes during your life."},{"time":501884,"text":"It gets shorter, you lose pieces,\nit gets insertions."},{"time":505190,"text":"We read the signals, and we make a model."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508438,"text":"Now, an interesting challenge:"},{"time":509937,"text":"Can we predict a human face?"},{"time":513014,"text":"It's a little complicated,"},{"time":514316,"text":"because a human face is scattered\namong millions of these letters."},{"time":517531,"text":"And a human face is not\na very well-defined object."},{"time":520184,"text":"So, we had to build an entire tier of it"},{"time":522259,"text":"to learn and teach\na machine what a face is,"},{"time":524993,"text":"and embed and compress it."},{"time":527054,"text":"And if you're comfortable\nwith machine learning,"},{"time":529326,"text":"you understand what the challenge is here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532108,"text":"Now, after 15 years -- 15 years after\nwe read the first sequence --"},{"time":538123,"text":"this October, we started\nto see some signals."},{"time":541049,"text":"And it was a very emotional moment."},{"time":543528,"text":"What you see here is a subject\ncoming in our lab."},{"time":547619,"text":"This is a face for us."},{"time":549571,"text":"So we take the real face of a subject,\nwe reduce the complexity,"},{"time":553226,"text":"because not everything is in your face --"},{"time":555220,"text":"lots of features and defects\nand asymmetries come from your life."},{"time":559030,"text":"We symmetrize the face,\nand we run our algorithm."},{"time":563245,"text":"The results that I show you right now,"},{"time":565167,"text":"this is the prediction we have\nfrom the blood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569596,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":571144,"text":"Wait a second."},{"time":572603,"text":"In these seconds, your eyes are watching,\nleft and right, left and right,"},{"time":577319,"text":"and your brain wants\nthose pictures to be identical."},{"time":581273,"text":"So I ask you to do\nanother exercise, to be honest."},{"time":583743,"text":"Please search for the differences,"},{"time":586054,"text":"which are many."},{"time":587439,"text":"The biggest amount of signal\ncomes from gender,"},{"time":590066,"text":"then there is age, BMI,\nthe ethnicity component of a human."},{"time":595291,"text":"And scaling up over that signal\nis much more complicated."},{"time":599026,"text":"But what you see here,\neven in the differences,"},{"time":602300,"text":"lets you understand\nthat we are in the right ballpark,"},{"time":605919,"text":"that we are getting closer."},{"time":607291,"text":"And it's already giving you some emotions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609664,"text":"This is another subject\nthat comes in place,"},{"time":612391,"text":"and this is a prediction."},{"time":613824,"text":"A little smaller face, we didn't get\nthe complete cranial structure,"},{"time":618444,"text":"but still, it's in the ballpark."},{"time":621634,"text":"This is a subject that comes in our lab,"},{"time":623882,"text":"and this is the prediction."},{"time":626056,"text":"So these people have never been seen\nin the training of the machine."},{"time":630756,"text":"These are the so-called \"held-out\" set."},{"time":633617,"text":"But these are people that you will\nprobably never believe."},{"time":637381,"text":"We're publishing everything\nin a scientific publication,"},{"time":640081,"text":"you can read it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641256,"text":"But since we are onstage,\nChris challenged me."},{"time":643624,"text":"I probably exposed myself\nand tried to predict"},{"time":647274,"text":"someone that you might recognize."},{"time":650470,"text":"So, in this vial of blood --\nand believe me, you have no idea"},{"time":654919,"text":"what we had to do to have\nthis blood now, here --"},{"time":657823,"text":"in this vial of blood is the amount\nof biological information"},{"time":661748,"text":"that we need to do a full genome sequence."},{"time":664049,"text":"We just need this amount."},{"time":666528,"text":"We ran this sequence,\nand I'm going to do it with you."},{"time":669757,"text":"And we start to layer up\nall the understanding we have."},{"time":673760,"text":"In the vial of blood,\nwe predicted he's a male."},{"time":677134,"text":"And the subject is a male."},{"time":678996,"text":"We predict that he's a meter and 76 cm."},{"time":681458,"text":"The subject is a meter and 77 cm."},{"time":683874,"text":"So, we predicted that he's 76;\nthe subject is 82."},{"time":688701,"text":"We predict his age, 38."},{"time":691357,"text":"The subject is 35."},{"time":693851,"text":"We predict his eye color."},{"time":696824,"text":"Too dark."},{"time":698059,"text":"We predict his skin color."},{"time":700026,"text":"We are almost there."},{"time":701899,"text":"That's his face."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705172,"text":"Now, the reveal moment:"},{"time":708465,"text":"the subject is this person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710259,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":712218,"text":"And I did it intentionally."},{"time":714300,"text":"I am a very particular\nand peculiar ethnicity."},{"time":718016,"text":"Southern European, Italians --\nthey never fit in models."},{"time":720990,"text":"And it's particular -- that ethnicity\nis a complex corner case for our model."},{"time":726144,"text":"But there is another point."},{"time":727677,"text":"So, one of the things that we use\na lot to recognize people"},{"time":731178,"text":"will never be written in the genome."},{"time":732924,"text":"It's our free will, it's how I look."},{"time":735265,"text":"Not my haircut in this case,\nbut my beard cut."},{"time":738518,"text":"So I'm going to show you, I'm going to,\nin this case, transfer it --"},{"time":742095,"text":"and this is nothing more\nthan Photoshop, no modeling --"},{"time":744884,"text":"the beard on the subject."},{"time":746621,"text":"And immediately, we get\nmuch, much better in the feeling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750955,"text":"So, why do we do this?"},{"time":755938,"text":"We certainly don't do it\nfor predicting height"},{"time":761102,"text":"or taking a beautiful picture\nout of your blood."},{"time":764390,"text":"We do it because the same technology\nand the same approach,"},{"time":768432,"text":"the machine learning of this code,"},{"time":770976,"text":"is helping us to understand how we work,"},{"time":774137,"text":"how your body works,"},{"time":775647,"text":"how your body ages,"},{"time":777336,"text":"how disease generates in your body,"},{"time":780129,"text":"how your cancer grows and develops,"},{"time":783125,"text":"how drugs work"},{"time":784932,"text":"and if they work on your body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787713,"text":"This is a huge challenge."},{"time":789894,"text":"This is a challenge that we share"},{"time":791556,"text":"with thousands of other\nresearchers around the world."},{"time":794159,"text":"It's called personalized medicine."},{"time":797125,"text":"It's the ability to move\nfrom a statistical approach"},{"time":800609,"text":"where you're a dot in the ocean,"},{"time":802665,"text":"to a personalized approach,"},{"time":804502,"text":"where we read all these books"},{"time":806711,"text":"and we get an understanding\nof exactly how you are."},{"time":810260,"text":"But it is a particularly\ncomplicated challenge,"},{"time":813646,"text":"because of all these books, as of today,"},{"time":817668,"text":"we just know probably two percent:"},{"time":821027,"text":"four books of more than 175."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826021,"text":"And this is not the topic of my talk,"},{"time":830145,"text":"because we will learn more."},{"time":833378,"text":"There are the best minds\nin the world on this topic."},{"time":837048,"text":"The prediction will get better,"},{"time":838906,"text":"the model will get more precise."},{"time":841183,"text":"And the more we learn,"},{"time":843065,"text":"the more we will\nbe confronted with decisions"},{"time":847919,"text":"that we never had to face before"},{"time":850964,"text":"about life,"},{"time":852423,"text":"about death,"},{"time":854121,"text":"about parenting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860626,"text":"So, we are touching the very\ninner detail on how life works."},{"time":866118,"text":"And it's a revolution\nthat cannot be confined"},{"time":869300,"text":"in the domain of science or technology."},{"time":872960,"text":"This must be a global conversation."},{"time":875798,"text":"We must start to think of the future\nwe're building as a humanity."},{"time":881039,"text":"We need to interact with creatives,\nwith artists, with philosophers,"},{"time":885127,"text":"with politicians."},{"time":886661,"text":"Everyone is involved,"},{"time":887843,"text":"because it's the future of our species."},{"time":891273,"text":"Without fear, but with the understanding"},{"time":895265,"text":"that the decisions\nthat we make in the next year"},{"time":899160,"text":"will change the course of history forever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903732,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904916,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}